üìñ The Story of Hamble Brook

The Hamble Brook flows through the Thames & S. Chilterns catchment, where our eDNA survey sampled 5 sites along its length. Analysis of water samples revealed a rich invertebrate community with 2,671 distinct genetic sequences (ESVs) representing 293 identified species and 159 families.

Compared to other chalk streams surveyed, the Hamble Brook shows moderate diversity compared to other rivers in the study (#9 of 10). The river supports 9 families of mayflies, stoneflies, and caddisflies (EPT) - key indicators of water quality.

Notable findings include the detection of conservation priority species (Water shrew) and invasive species requiring management attention.
